abstract: The Bank of England's admission that a technical supplier leaked audio feeds from its news conferences throws a spotlight on financial markets' insatiable appetite for speed and lucrative information their rivals don't yet have.
snippet: The Bank of England's admission that a technical supplier leaked audio feeds from its news conferences throws a spotlight on financial markets' insatiable appetite for speed and lucrative information their rivals don't yet have.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The Bank of England's admission that a technical supplier leaked audio feeds from its news conferences throws a spotlight on financial markets' insatiable appetite for speed and lucrative information their rivals don't yet have.
headline_main: Explainer: What BoE Audio Leak Says About the Information Arms Race in Markets
headline_print_headline: Explainer: What BoE Audio Leak Says About the Information Arms Race in Markets

abstract: Five senators and two members of the House of Representatives asked Jamie Dimon to list the bank’s run-ins with authorities over discrimination and explain how it plans to do better.
snippet: Five senators and two members of the House of Representatives asked Jamie Dimon to list the bank’s run-ins with authorities over discrimination and explain how it plans to do better.
lead_paragraph: Democratic lawmakers, five from the Senate and two from the House of Representatives, asked Jamie Dimon, the chief executive of JPMorgan Chase, to list steps the bank is taking to combat discrimination against black customers and employees following a New York Times report about racism at some of the bank’s branches in Arizona.

abstract: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending the impeachment articles to the Senate risks eating further into senators' final weeks of campaigning for the Democratic presidential nomination before the first caucus in February.
snippet: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending the impeachment articles to the Senate risks eating further into senators' final weeks of campaigning for the Democratic presidential nomination before the first caucus in February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending the impeachment articles to the Senate risks eating further into senators' final weeks of campaigning for the Democratic presidential nomination before the first caucus in February.
